{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842706701,"sessionID":"ses_287880798ffeX8tFn1HdwnFoQp","part":{"id":"prt_d787872be001dq0OJtpHVNQ5ns","messageID":"msg_d7878642e001Eak9KyrLOTS2zX","sessionID":"ses_287880798ffeX8tFn1HdwnFoQp","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_98f1f5827e9a42ecbe455bfd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-005: Sandbox 创建处理器 (Sandbox Creation Processor)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-005\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe WorkloadManager module provides a high-level abstraction layer for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the agentcube system. It wraps the generated client-go library and exposes a clean interface for CRUD operations and watching resources.\n\n### 1.2 Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── client.go          # Kubernetes client initialization\n├── service.go         # WorkloadManager interface and implementation\n├── server.go          # HTTP server for workload management API\n├── types.go           # Request/Response types and error handling\n└── design.md          # This design document\n```\n\n### 1.3 Layered Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            HTTP API Layer               │\n│           (server.go)                   │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│          Service Layer                  │\n│      (WorkloadManager interface)        │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│         Client Layer                    │\n│     (versioned.Interface wrapper)       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│      Generated client-go                │\n│  github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Core Types\n\n#### K8sClient\n```go\ntype K8sClient struct {\n    Clientset        versioned.Interface\n    DynamicClient    dynamic.Interface\n    KubernetesClient *kubernetes.Clientset\n}\n```\n- **Purpose**: Holds all Kubernetes client instances\n- **Lifecycle**: Created on startup, closed on shutdown\n\n#### WorkloadManager Interface\n```go\ntype WorkloadManager interface {\n    // AgentRuntime operations\n    CreateAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace string, agentRuntime *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    ListAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context, namespace string, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    UpdateAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace string, agentRuntime *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    DeleteAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    GetAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus, error)\n    PatchAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context, namespace string, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n\n    // CodeInterpreter operations\n    CreateCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace string, codeInterpreter *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    ListCodeInterpreters(ctx context.Context, namespace string, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterList, error)\n    UpdateCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace string, codeInterpreter *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    DeleteCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    GetCodeInterpreterStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterStatus, error)\n    PatchCodeInterpreterStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    WatchCodeInterpreters(ctx context.Context, namespace string, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Request/Response Types\n\n| Type | File | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| APIResponse | types.go | Standard API response wrapper |\n| APIError | types.go | Standard error response |\n| ListMeta | types.go | Pagination metadata |\n| PaginationRequest | types.go | Query parameters for list operations |\n| AgentRuntimeListResponse | types.go | AgentRuntime list response |\n| CodeInterpreterListResponse | types.go | CodeInterpreter list response |\n| CreateAgentRuntimeRequest | types.go | AgentRuntime creation request |\n| CreateCodeInterpreterRequest | types.go | CodeInterpreter creation request |\n| WatchEvent | types.go | Watch event wrapper |\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Client Initialization\n\n#### NewK8sClient\n```go\nfunc NewK8sClient(kubeconfig string) (*K8sClient, error)\n```\n- **Parameters**: \n  - `kubeconfig`: Path to kubeconfig file, or empty string for default, or \"in-cluster\" for in-cluster mode\n- **Returns**: Initialized K8sClient with all client instances\n- **Errors**: Configuration loading errors, client creation errors\n\n#### NewInClusterClient\n```go\nfunc NewInClusterClient() (*K8sClient, error)\n```\n- **Purpose**: Convenience method for in-cluster deployment\n- **Returns**: Client configured from service account\n\n### 3.2 AgentRuntime Operations\n\n| Operation | Method | Resource Path |\n|-----------|--------|---------------|\n| Create | POST | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes |\n| Get | GET | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name} |\n| List | GET | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes |\n| Update | PUT | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name} |\n| Delete | DELETE | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name} |\n| Watch | GET (watch=true) | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes?watch=true |\n| Patch Status | PATCH | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status |\n\n### 3.3 CodeInterpreter Operations\n\nSame REST paths as AgentRuntime, with resource name `codeinterpreters`.\n\n### 3.4 Query Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| labelSelector | string | Label selector for filtering |\n| fieldSelector | string | Field selector for filtering |\n| watch | bool | Enable watch mode |\n| timeoutSeconds | int64 | Timeout for watch/list operations |\n| limit | int64 | Limit number of results |\n| continue | string | Continue token for pagination |\n| resourceVersion | string | Resource version for read consistency |\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Error Types\n\n| Error Code | Reason | Description |\n|------------|--------|-------------|\n| 400 | BadRequest | Invalid request format |\n| 404 | NotFound | Resource not found |\n| 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n| 422 | Invalid | Validation failed |\n| 500 | InternalError | Server error |\n| 503 | ServiceUnavailable | Cluster unavailable |\n\n### 4.2 Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"kind\": \"Status\",\n  \"apiVersion\": \"v1\",\n  \"status\": \"Failure\",\n  \"message\": \"resource not found\",\n  \"reason\": \"NotFound\",\n  \"code\": 404,\n  \"details\": {\n    \"name\": \"my-runtime\",\n    \"kind\": \"agentruntime\",\n    \"causes\": [\n      {\n        \"message\": \"AgentRuntime.agentcube.volcano.sh \\\"my-runtime\\\" not found\",\n        \"field\": \"metadata.name\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 4.3 Error Translation\n\nAll Kubernetes API errors are wrapped with context and propagated to callers. Errors include:\n- Resource name and namespace in error message\n- Original error as wrapped cause\n- Appropriate HTTP status codes\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Tests\n\n#### Client Initialization Tests\n- Test kubeconfig loading from default path\n- Test in-cluster config loading\n- Test error handling for invalid kubeconfig\n- Test client creation failures\n\n#### Service Operation Tests\n- Test CRUD operations with mock client\n- Test error propagation from client layer\n- Test context cancellation handling\n\n### 5.2 Integration Tests\n\n- Test against real Kubernetes cluster (optional)\n- Test with fake clientset for controlled environment\n- Test resource lifecycle (create → get → update → delete)\n\n### 5.3 Fake Client Usage\n\nThe generated fake clientset should be used for testing:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    fakeagentcube \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n)\n\nfunc TestWorkloadManager(t *testing.T) {\n    client := fakeagentcube.NewSimpleClientset()\n    k8s := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n    \n    wm := workloadmanager.NewWorkloadManager(client)\n    \n    // Test operations\n    ar, err := wm.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, \"default\", agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    // assertions...\n}\n```\n\n### 5.4 Test Coverage Targets\n\n| Component | Target Coverage |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| client.go | 80% |\n| service.go | 85% |\n| types.go | 90% |\n| server.go | 75% |\n\n## 6. Dependencies\n\n### 6.1 Direct Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| k8s.io/client-go | latest | Kubernetes client infrastructure |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery | latest | API types and utilities |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | latest | Logging |\n\n### 6.2 Internal Dependencies\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | Generated client library |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | API types |\n\n## 7. Configuration\n\n### 7.1 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| KUBECONFIG | ~/.kube/config | Path to kubeconfig |\n| IN_CLUSTER | false | Use in-cluster config |\n\n### 7.2 Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| kubeconfig | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig |\n| master | string | \"\" | Kubernetes API server |\n\n## 8. Performance Considerations\n\n### 8.1 Client Caching\n\n- Reuse client instances across requests\n- Client initialization is expensive; cache at module level\n\n### 8.2 List Operations\n\n- Use pagination for large result sets\n- Set reasonable timeouts (default: 30s)\n\n### 8.3 Watch Connections\n\n- Implement reconnection logic for watch operations\n- Set appropriate timeout values\n- Clean up watch connections on client close\n\n## 9. Security\n\n### 9.1 RBAC Requirements\n\nThe WorkloadManager requires the following RBAC permissions:\n\n```yaml\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n```\n\n### 9.2 Credentials\n\n- Use service account credentials when running in-cluster\n- Support kubeconfig with arbitrary authentication methods\n- Never log or expose credentials\n\n## 10. References\n\n- [client-go library](../deployment/client-go.md)\n- [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n- [code-generator usage](https://git.k8s.io/code-generator)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server.go\">\nERROR [13:2] could not import github.com/gin-gonic/gin (no required module provides package \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\")\nERROR [64:58] server.handleListAgentRuntimes undefined (type *Server has no field or method handleListAgentRuntimes)\nERROR [65:59] server.handleCreateAgentRuntime undefined (type *Server has no field or method handleCreateAgentRuntime)\nERROR [66:64] server.handleGetAgentRuntime undefined (type *Server has no field or method handleGetAgentRuntime)\nERROR [67:64] server.handleUpdateAgentRuntime undefined (type *Server has no field or method handleUpdateAgentRuntime)\nERROR [68:67] server.handleDeleteAgentRuntime undefined (type *Server has no field or method handleDeleteAgentRuntime)\nERROR [69:71] server.handleGetAgentRuntimeStatus undefined (type *Server has no field or method handleGetAgentRuntimeStatus)\nERROR [70:73] server.handlePatchAgentRuntimeStatus undefined (type *Server has no field or method handlePatchAgentRuntimeStatus)\nERROR [72:61] server.handleListCodeInterpreters undefined (type *Server has no field or method handleListCodeInterpreters)\nERROR [73:62] server.handleCreateCodeInterpreter undefined (type *Server has no field or method handleCreateCodeInterpreter)\nERROR [74:67] server.handleGetCodeInterpreter undefined (type *Server has no field or method handleGetCodeInterpreter)\nER